So, I couldn't and cannot emphasize enough how good this album is. Some of my favorite artists have released AMAZING albums this year (@_fake_nudes_ @thelawrencearms  @brighteyesofficial @dasowth.sgh ), but I didn't even KNOW SLS before 2020. This is still my favorite, and arguably one of the most relevant, important albums, of recent memory. It's VERY familiar to me, but entirely different and new. It's a non-genre in a micro sense. Is it "post-emo" or "punk" or "indie alternative?" Who cares? I promise if you like any of the tagged artists or @sayanything or @jawbreakerband or @huskerduofficial or @twiabp or @takingbacksunday or anything REMOTELY in that ballpark/ game, try it. Oh and if you are between the ages of 0-40: CONGRATULATIONS- the lyrical content will slap you in the face over and over. Don't thank me.
